AB  - Contingent credit lines (CCLs) are widely used in bank lending and also play an important role in the functioning of short-term capital markets. Yet their pricing and hedging has not received much attention in the finance literature. Using a financial engineering approach, the article analyzes the structure of simple CCLs, examines methods for their pricing, and discusses the problems faced in hedging CCL portfolios. Copyright © 2004 Institutional Investor, Inc. All Rights Reserved.
