AB  - This study aims to understand an effective model of mathematical meaning-making in classrooms with a majority of Latina/o English learners. This analysis is grounded in the cultural-historical ideas that learning is mediated through organized activity and learners show greater awareness of problem-solving strategies through metadiscourse practices. In particular, we focus on the use of discussion builder stems and OK/Pitfall stories to mediate discussions and develop metacognitive awareness for English learners. © OISE.
