TI  - Hedging of exchange rate risk of agricultural products import
PY  - 2020
JO  - International Agricultural Engineering Journal
AB  - Based on the new measure CVaRMD proposed by Yu, Zhang & Liu (2018), this paper investigated the currency options hedging problem for a firm engaged in agricultural products import under the risk of exchange rate. The optimal currency options hedging model was presented when the exchange rate option market existed. The cumulative distribution functions of the hedged portfolio with options were deduced through a copula function. The Copula-GARCH method was employed to solve the hedging problems. The empirical studies demonstrated that GARCH-n and GARCH-t models are respectively better to forecast soya-bean price and the exchange rate (CNY/USD) volatilities. Frank copula could better portray the correlation structure between soya-bean price and the exchange rate. By comparing the extreme loss skewness under risk measures of Conditional value-at-risk (CVaR), median deviation (MD) and CVaRMD, we found that the degree of left deviation under the new risk measure of CVaRMD was the greatest. Based on the strategy of minimizing CVaRMD, the extreme loss risk that the firm faced is relatively small. © 2020, Asian Association for Agricultural Engineering. All rights reserved.
